21/12/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- UNMIK announced on Wednesday (December 20th) that UN police, together with KFOR and the Kosovo Police Service (KPS), are strengthening security in the province.
According to the statement, efforts are focused particularly on preventing ethnically or politically motivated violence.
In other news, the KPS reportedly seized weapons, explosives and ammunition from a car in the Glogovac municipality village of Sutica, Wednesday night.
Three people were arrested, including one government official.
An investigation is under way.
(Tanjug, RTS - 20/12/06)
